But so far, the CERN has not found such differences.
Consequences
It is more difficult to predict from these studies for the daily life of the average human being, but it would be a mistake to assume that they are not.
Look, early in the 1960s, pioneers in laser research at Bella's labs couldn't even imagine what kind of revolution their work would trigger.
They anticipated their applications in science, but nothing more.
