"The usual bookshelves stand along the facades, and in the middle there is a large dark hall, usually uncomfortable and faceless," says Vinie Maas.
We put the classical configuration of space on top of the head and pulled out the reading area from the outside.
The inner area of the book mountain has been used skillfully: the centre has offices, an Internet library, a chess club, an environmental centre and technical facilities.
The black bookshelves, which serve as wallworks, parapets, and staircases, are particularly refreshing.
